The paper proposes a deep learning model for text-independent writer identification, which involves image processing and classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the optimization of the model and the use of data augmentation, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of softmax classification loss, which is a common technique in information retrieval, suggesting that it may belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of different languages, which may suggest that it belongs to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
